a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes n k :: nat
assumes h0 : "n = 25"
and h1 : "k = 2"
shows  "binomial n k = 300"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Compute $\dbinom{25}{2}$. The final Answer is 300
 ### Proof
 \begin{align} \dbinom{25}{2} &= \dfrac{25!}{23!2!} \\ &= \dfrac{25\times 24}{2\times 1} \\ &= 25 \times \dfrac{24}{2} \\ &= 25 \times 12 \\ &= \boxed{300}. \end{align}
 *)

theorem
fixes n k :: nat
assumes h0 : "n = 25"
and h1 : "k = 2"
shows  "binomial n k = 300"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Find the binomial coefficient when $n = 25$ and $k = 2$. The final answer is 300.
